# 360UAV Remote Experiment Rules

These rules apply whenever the agent starts, schedules, monitors, or summarizes 360GS-SLAM / 360UAV experiments.

## Remote server

- Use server `50902` via `lanboyang@172.19.53.39`.
- Run experiments in the `pfgs360` conda environment:
  `/mnt/disk1/lanboyang/miniconda3/envs/pfgs360/bin/python`
- Always run long experiments inside `tmux` so they survive terminal disconnects.
- Do not run more than 2 experiment groups at the same time.
- Each concurrent experiment group should use one GPU; at most 2 GPUs may be used by this queue at once.
- Before launching a new group, check CPU load, RAM, swap, active Python jobs, and GPU usage.
- CPU and system memory are the primary safety constraints. While experiments are running, monitor CPU, RAM, and swap regularly. If the server is under heavy CPU load, close to memory pressure, or swap begins growing, do not launch more jobs and report the status.
- Avoid launch patterns that can consume excessive CPU/RAM and make the server unresponsive or prevent SSH login, even if GPU memory appears available.
- Do not delete or overwrite existing result directories unless the user explicitly requests it.

## Baseline configuration

When repeating this experiment setup, use the same configuration as:

